<p>The Song of Jacob Zulu</h1></p>

<p>From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</p>


<ref class="mw-jump-link" href="#mw-head">Jump to navigation</ref>
<ref class="mw-jump-link" href="#p-search">Jump to search</ref>
<p>The Song of Jacob Zulu is an American play that debuted on <ref target="/wiki/Broadway_theatre" title="Broadway theatre">Broadway</ref> in 1993. Written by <ref target="/wiki/Tug_Yourgrau" title="Tug Yourgrau">Tug Yourgrau</ref>, with music and lyrics by <ref target="/wiki/Ladysmith_Black_Mambazo" title="Ladysmith Black Mambazo">Ladysmith Black Mambazo</ref>, and produced by the <ref target="/wiki/Steppenwolf_Theatre_Company" title="Steppenwolf Theatre Company">Steppenwolf Theatre Company</ref>, the play is a drama set during <ref target="/wiki/Apartheid" title="Apartheid">Apartheid</ref> in <ref target="/wiki/South_Africa" title="South Africa">South Africa</ref>.<ref target="#cite_note-1">[1]</ref><ref target="#cite_note-2">[2]</ref> The play's Broadway production was nominated for six <ref target="/wiki/Tony_Award" title="Tony Award">Tony Awards</ref>,<ref target="#cite_note-3">[3]</ref> including <ref target="/wiki/Tony_Award_for_Best_Play" title="Tony Award for Best Play">Best Play</ref>, <ref target="/wiki/Tony_Award_for_Best_Actor_in_a_Play" title="Tony Award for Best Actor in a Play">Best Actor in a Play</ref> for <ref target="/wiki/K._Todd_Freeman" title="K. Todd Freeman">K. Todd Freeman</ref>, and <ref target="/wiki/Tony_Award_for_Best_Featured_Actor_in_a_Play" title="Tony Award for Best Featured Actor in a Play">Best Featured Actor in a Play</ref> for <ref target="/wiki/Zakes_Mokae" title="Zakes Mokae">Zakes Mokae</ref>.</p>

